#!/usr/bin/env eu
# eu-2sa6 — branch-gated self-recursion demand regression (Wicket review of PR #1016).
#
# Wicket's review of PR #1016 flagged this exact shape: a *documented*
# (Meta-wrapped -- carrying a `doc`/`type` backtick annotation) self-recursive
# function whose cond/pattern-match branches only SOME of which reference the
# locally-bound recursive calls. The worry: eager-argument resolution for
# self-recursive DirectApp calls (an optimisation that avoids O(n^2)
# indirection build-up across iterations, see src/eval/stg/compiler.rs) might
# force every locally-bound recursive call unconditionally at each
# invocation, even on a branch that references neither -- turning a
# terminating lazy recursion into non-termination (unbounded native
# recursion, observed as a stack overflow) instead of merely returning a
# wrong answer.
#
# This mirrors lib/reflect.eu exactly: `from-data(td)` is a documented,
# Meta-wrapped top-level binding whose body defines a nested, self-recursive
# local `to-str[tag:rest]` with `r0`/`r1`/`s0`/`s1` bindings feeding a cond,
# where some branches use only one of `s0`/`s1` and some use neither. The
# bug (if present) would live in how `compile_binding` threads self-recursion
# context through the OUTER Meta wrapper into the INNER self-recursive local.
#
# `bomb` recurses on itself with no base case reachable through its own
# argument -- if ever forced it either panics (destructuring a non-list) or
# diverges; either way the test fails loudly and promptly rather than
# hanging, which is more CI-friendly than an open-ended non-terminating
# check while testing exactly the same property: whether laziness holds.
# The `:leaf` branch references neither `s0` nor `s1`, so under correct lazy
# semantics `bomb` must never be forced and the recursion must terminate via
# the reachable base case.

` { doc: "`describe(td)` - render a small synthetic tagged tree, mirroring
         lib/reflect.eu's `from-data`/`to-str[tag:rest]` nesting shape:
         a documented top-level function wrapping a nested, cond-gated
         self-recursive local."
    type: s"any → any" }
describe(td):
  { bomb(x): bomb(x)

    to-str[tag : rest]:
      { r0: rest first
        r1: rest second
        s0: to-str(r0)
        s1: bomb(r1)
      }.(cond[
          tag = :leaf => "leaf"
        , tag = :node => "{s0}-{s1}"
        , "unreachable"
        ])
  }.(to-str(td))

RESULT: (describe([:leaf, [:node, 1, 2], 42]) = "leaf") then(:PASS, :FAIL)
